# Windows Server and Active Directory Environment Build

## Overview

This project documents the deployment of a small Windows enterprise environment using VMware Workstation.

The lab includes a Windows Server domain controller, a domain-joined Windows workstation, and a Windows Server member server. The environment supports centralized authentication, user and computer management, DNS, DHCP, routing, and future Group Policy and access-control exercises.

## Objectives

- Build an isolated Windows domain environment
- Deploy Active Directory Domain Services
- Configure DNS and DHCP
- Join Windows systems to the domain
- Practice centralized identity administration
- Develop Windows and network troubleshooting skills
- Create a foundation for additional IT support and security labs

